"children":[
"Calcium Pyrophosphate Deposition"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_rm_s12_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1896c3",
"children":[
"The four clinical presentations of ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"calcium pyrophosphate deposition",
"children":[
"CPPD"
]
},
" are:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"de0af0",
"children":[
"asymptomatic (chondrocalcinosis/cartilage calcification)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"95de43",
"children":[
"acute ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"calcium pyrophosphate",
"children":[
"CPP"
]
},
" crystal arthritis (pseudogout)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"16ef75",
"children":[
"chronic CPP crystal inflammatory arthritis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"41a12d",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"osteoarthritis",
"children":[
"OA"
]
},
" with CPPD"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8e8988",
"children":[
"Characteristic findings in acute CPP crystal arthritis (pseudogout) are:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"867888",
"children":[
"inflammation localized to one joint, affecting the knee, wrist, shoulder, or ankle"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c2dd0b",
"children":[
"acute onset of several painful joints following trauma, severe illness, or surgery"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"177f0d",
"children":[
"rhomboid-shaped, positively birefringent synovial fluid crystals"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a1865e",
"children":[
"Characteristic findings in chronic CPP crystal arthropathy include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9dc1b0",
"children":[
"two distinct patterns: chronic CPP crystal inflammatory arthritis and OA with CPPD"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"933fa1",
"children":[
"chronic CPP crystal inflammatory arthritis resembles ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"rheumatoid arthritis",
"children":[
"RA"
]
}
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"be99a4",
"children":[
"OA with CPPD exhibits OA findings in atypical locations including wrist, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"metacarpophalangeal",
"children":[
"MCP"
]
},
","
]
},
" or shoulder joints"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"060bfd",
"children":[
"Characteristic findings in asymptomatic CPPD are:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fcbe16",
"children":[
"triangular fibrocartilage of the wrist joint (space between the carpal bones and distal ulna)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"441238",
"children":[
"menisci of the knee joint (appearing as a line in the cartilage)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"853158",
"children":[
"symphysis pubis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"eaf178",
"children":[
"CPPD may be associated with underlying metabolic disorders. Screen patients with CPPD who are <50 years of age for:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a29bb3",
"children":[
"hemochromatosis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"6cc375",
"children":[
"hypomagnesemia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"dc3991",
"children":[
"hyperparathyroidism"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"78c24e",
"children":[
"hypothyroidism"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_rm_f16"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"579de9",
"children":[
"The absence of chondrocalcinosis on x-ray does not rule out CPPD."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_rm_s12_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f821ce",
"children":[
"For acute CPPD, local treatment is intra-articular glucocorticoid injection; systemic treatment includes ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs",
"children":[
"NSAIDs"
]
},
","
]
},
" colchicine, and glucocorticoids (oral, intramuscular, or parenteral). For chronic inflammatory CPP, choose low-dose colchicine, low-dose NSAIDs, or low-dose glucocorticoids. For OA with CPP, treatment is the same as for OA without CPPD."
]
}
]
}
]
},
